<subSubSection id="C33311E1FFE47F0D99F7E22DD7F1FD45" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFE47F0D99F7E22DD59DFE10" blockId="33.[151,1436,229,751]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE47F0D99F7E22DD503FEC6" bold="true" box="[198,529,338,364]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Distribution and ecology:</emphasis>
—Local and apparently disjunct in western 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE47F0D9D0DE22DD3A2FEC6" box="[1084,1200,338,364]" name="Colombia" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49ED8C88FFE47F0D9DF6E22DD20CFEC6" box="[1223,1310,338,364]" country="Colombia" name="Narino" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Nariño</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE47F0D9C08E22DD285FEC6" box="[1337,1431,338,364]" name="Guyana" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE47F0D99A6E206D7E9FE39" box="[151,251,377,403]" name="Ecuador" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE47F0D9834E206D62CFE39" box="[261,318,377,403]" name="Peru" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE47F0D984BE206D6C2FE39" box="[378,464,377,403]" name="Bolivia" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(La Paz). It is locally common (especially in 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE47F0D9AD0E206D356FE39" box="[993,1092,377,403]" name="Ecuador" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
) on roadbanks and landslides in humid montane forests at 
<quantity id="4CD1EF8FFFE47F0D98D4E2DFD598FE10" box="[485,650,416,442]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.95" metricValueMin="1.95" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="m" value="2450.0" valueMax="2950.0" valueMin="1950.0">1950–2950 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96426AFFE47F0D99F7E2B9D7F1FD45" blockId="33.[151,1436,229,751]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE47F0D99F7E2B9D607FE4A" bold="true" box="[198,277,454,480]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB83F9BFFE47F0D9802E2B9D5AFFE4A" author="Ostergaard A. &amp; Ollgaard, E." box="[307,701,454,480]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="107 - 169" refId="ref33047" refString="Ostergaard A., Ollgaard, E. &amp; B. (2001) Gleicheniaceae. In Harling, G. &amp; Andersson, L. (eds.), Flora of Ecuador 66: 107 - 169." type="journal article" year="2001">Østergaard &amp; Øllgaard (2001)</bibRefCitation>
recognized the morphological intermediacy between 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE47F0D9CB7E2B8D654FDAC" authorityName="Ostergaard &amp; Ollgaard" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Alston" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="melanoblastus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE47F0D9CB7E2B8D654FDAC" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S. melanoblastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE47F0D98B2E292D538FDAC" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="Cav. ex Sw." box="[387,554,493,518]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tomentosus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE47F0D98B2E292D538FDAC" box="[387,554,493,518]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S. tomentosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of a speciemn from 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE47F0D9A1BE292D49CFDAD" box="[810,910,493,519]" name="Ecuador" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49ED8C88FFE47F0D9A91E292D4CCFDAD" box="[928,990,493,519]" country="Ecuador" name="Loja" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Loja</collectingRegion>
: trail ca. 
<quantity id="4CD1EF8FFFE47F0D9D7EE292D39FFDAD" box="[1103,1165,493,519]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="km" value="5.0">5 km</quantity>
ENE of 
<collectingCountry id="F33E02FAFFE47F0D9DCBE292D265FDAD" box="[1274,1399,493,519]" name="Saint Pierre and Miquelon" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">San Pedro</collectingCountry>
de Vilcabamba, from “El Bosque” to Quebrada Romerillos, 
<quantity id="4CD1EF8FFFE47F0D9A6EE16BD31EFD84" box="[863,1036,532,558]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="m" value="2150.0" valueMax="2200.0" valueMin="2100.0">2100–2200 m</quantity>
, 
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE47F0D9D2BE16BD281FD87" box="[1050,1427,532,557]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Øllgaard &amp; Navarrete 105881</emphasis>
, AAU). However, they hesitated to designate it as a hybrid because the spores appeared normal. Yet, normal spores have also been observed in other hybrid specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2939E9FFE47F0D9A5AE11ED4C5FDD0" authorityName="Presl" authorityYear="1836" box="[875,983,609,634]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Gleicheniaceae" genus="Sticherus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gleicheniales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95D9E78FFE47F0D9A5AE11ED4C5FDD0" box="[875,983,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Sticherus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other characters (intermediate morphology) strongly suggest hybridization. The specimen has hybrid vigor (segments to 
<quantity id="4CD1EF8FFFE47F0D9DE1E1F7D230FD08" box="[1232,1314,648,674]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="cm" value="8.5">8.5 cm</quantity>
long) and grew as a single individual among a large mixed population of the putative parents (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB83F9BFFE47F0D9DB8E1D1D7C4FD45" author="Ostergaard A. &amp; Ollgaard, E." pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="107 - 169" refId="ref33047" refString="Ostergaard A., Ollgaard, E. &amp; B. (2001) Gleicheniaceae. In Harling, G. &amp; Andersson, L. (eds.), Flora of Ecuador 66: 107 - 169." type="journal article" year="2001">Østergaard &amp; Øllgaard 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
